Migration information for hackers:

1.0.1 -> 1.0.2 (WIP):
    epameny now has one command-line argument which is only parsed as such when
    it is the sole argument: `-` (dash). When this condition is met, items are
    read from stdin.
    This introduces an (unlikely but possible) incompatibility in simple-mode
    (meny_simple=1) where this mode (reading from stdin) is incorrectly
    triggered if there only is one valid input which happens to be `-`.

    In other words, this test will fail:

        mkdir emptyDirectory
        cd emptyDirectory
        mkdir '-'
        meny_simple=1 epameny $(ls -1)

    If this condition is something you're worried about, you will now have to
    check for and handle this condition somehow; for example by surrounding
    the input in quotes.
    Alternatively, and perhaps more reasonably if the use-case is this
    advanced, Epameny's normal mode should be used instead of simple mode.


1.0 -> 1.0.1:
    Label formatting
    ----------------
    meny_sel_[beg/end] & meny_nsel_[beg/end] have been combined into
    meny_pickfmt & meny_normfmt. Effectively,

        meny_pickfmt="${meny_sel_beg}::label::${meny_sel_end}"
        meny_normfmt="${meny_nsel_beg}::label::${meny_nsel_end}"

    Epameny replaces '::label::' with the item's label.

    This prior code:
        meny_sel_beg='->'
        meny_sel_end='<-'
        meny_nsel_beg='  '
        meny_nsel_end=' meh'

    Should be rewritten as:

        meny_pickfmt='->::label::<-'
        meny_normfmt='  ::label:: meh'
